<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id8e81186a-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s212"><num value="212">§ 212.</num><heading> Persons entitled to passport</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">No passport shall be granted or issued to or verified for any other persons than those owing allegiance, whether citizens or not, to the United States.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id8e81186b-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">(R.S. § 4076; <ref href="/us/act/1902-06-14/ch1088/s2">June 14, 1902, ch. 1088, § 2</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/32/386">32 Stat. 386</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id8e81186c-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id8e81186d-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="id8e81186e-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">R.S. § 4076 derived from <ref href="/us/act/1866-05-30/ch102">act May 30, 1866, ch. 102</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/14/54">14 Stat. 54</ref>.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id8e81186f-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1902—Act <date date="1902-06-14">June 14, 1902</date>, substituted “those owing allegiance, whether citizens or not, to the United States” for “citizens of the United States”.</p>
</note>
</notes>
